The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Sunday, May 6, 2007

 Soccer

 Enjoy The Telegraph Cup Football at CC amp;FC.

 Word power

 Attend the launch of India After Gandhi: The History of the Worlds Largest Democracy by Ramachandra Guha at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm. 

 Drop in at an exhibition of books by and on Rabindranath Tagore at Rabindra Charcha Bhavan, Kalighat, 2 pm-8 pm. 

 Screen amp; Stage

 Enjoy screenings at Nandan II and Satyajit Ray Film and Television Institute as part of an Assamese film festival, from 1.30 pm. 

 Listen to the annual concert of Talent City at the Science City auditorium, 2 pm. 

 Eye on art

 Browse through an exhibition of sculptures by Sankho Chaudhuri at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 8 pm. 

 Move on to Landscape in Modern Paintings, curated by Prasanta Daw, at Aakriti Art Gallery, 3 pm to 7 pm. 




